---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="Which Country Has the Best Ecommerce Infrastructure? - parcelLab"
  description="The Netherlands leads the UN's B2C E-commerce Index, with 8 European countries in the top 10. Explore what makes a nation's ecommerce infrastructure world-class."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Research</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">Which Country Has the Best Ecommerce Infrastructure?</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">parcelLab Team</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2019-02-28">February 28, 2019</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>5 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          Online commerce continues expanding globally. According to the UN's B2C E-commerce Index, the Netherlands currently ranks as the country with the best ecommerce infrastructure. The Index evaluates 151 nations using indicators including postal reliability, internet usage rates, and secure server availability.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Europe Leads the Way</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Eight European countries occupy the top 10 positions for ecommerce infrastructure quality. Despite Luxembourg's previous first-place ranking, it dropped to 19th due to declining postal service dependability.
        </p>

        <div class="my-10 rounded-2xl bg-[var(--surface-sunken)] p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Top 10 Rankings</p>
          <ol class="mt-4 space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--ink)]"><span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3] text-xs font-bold text-white">1</span> Netherlands</li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--ink)]"><span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/80 text-xs font-bold text-white">2</span> Singapore</li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--ink)]"><span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/70 text-xs font-bold text-white">3</span> Switzerland</li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--ink)]"><span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/60 text-xs font-bold text-white">4</span> United Kingdom</li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--ink)]"><span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/50 text-xs font-bold text-white">5</span> Norway</li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--ink)]"><span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/40 text-xs font-bold text-white">6</span> Iceland</li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--ink)]"><span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/30 text-xs font-bold text-white">7</span> Ireland</li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--ink)]"><span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/25 text-xs font-bold text-white">8</span> Sweden</li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--ink)]"><span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/20 text-xs font-bold text-white">9</span> New Zealand</li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--ink)]"><span class="flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/15 text-xs font-bold text-white">10</span> Denmark</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Security Counts</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          The Netherlands excels particularly in secure server infrastructure. Secure servers serve as a proxy for ecommerce shops, and the nation hosted over 40,000 pure-play online retailers in 2016 -- the EU's highest figure.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          The country also boasts the second-highest proportion of online shoppers (76% of those aged 15+). The UK ranks fourth overall, benefiting from strong postal reliability and widespread ecommerce account adoption. Britain generates the highest annual online spending in Europe, representing 7.3% of GDP.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">The Asian Angle</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Singapore represents Asia's highest-ranking nation, improving from 18th place previously. It shares top postal reliability ratings alongside Ireland. Other leading Asian markets -- Hong Kong and South Korea -- demonstrate strong ecommerce infrastructure capabilities as well.
        </p>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          The ranking reveals that ecommerce success is not just about technology -- it depends equally on postal reliability, internet penetration, and secure infrastructure. For retailers expanding internationally, understanding these infrastructure differences is critical to delivering consistent customer experiences across markets.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
